    InvalidFunctionException is a subclass of RuntimeException, upon which it is thrown if the custom function calls another custom function inside itself (iterative/recursive) or if there are any errors with the function definition (name and parameters included).

    InvalidKeyWordException
    InvalidKeyWordException is a subclass of RuntimeException, upon which it is thrown if the user's custom function utilizes another custom function's signature (note: this does not include the function's arguments, only the function name).
    InvalidPairingException
